The paper discusses a system for scalable interactive graph visualization and mining, which involves handling large graphs and implementing algorithms for summarization and multi-resolution. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.IR (information retrieval), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.CG (computational geometry). However, given the focus on graph visualization and mining, cs.DB and cs.SI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.IR, cs.DS, and cs.CG.
